cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper deals with learning probabilistic models over strings using spectral methods, which involves matrix decomposition and concentration bounds. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the use of automata and inference, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
